{#def action="/screen", target="#flow", swap="beforeend" #}
{# HTMX form primitive: posts to `action`, appends the response as a
   new child of `target`, and toggles any nested `.spinner` (see
   SubmitButton) while the request is in flight. Once a submission
   succeeds, this form's own fields are disabled — it reads as a sent
   message in the transcript rather than a live, resubmittable form
   sitting in the middle of it. Extra attributes (class, id, ...)
   pass through.

   `target` defaults to `#flow`, the running conversation log
   (initial form, Clarify, Confirm, Results, ... each appended in
   turn) — never replaced, only ever added to.

   `hx-sync="this:drop"` drops re-submissions while a request is in
   flight — without it a double-click aborts and re-issues the
   request, costing a duplicate LLM/search round server-side.

   Handled errors come back as HTTP 200 with an X-OpenHand-Error
   header (see `_error_alert` in the screen router) — those must NOT
   disable the form, or the "please try again" alert would sit next
   to a form the person can no longer resubmit. #}
<form hx-post="{{ action }}" hx-target="{{ target }}"
      hx-swap="{{ swap }}" hx-indicator="this" hx-sync="this:drop"
      hx-on::after-request="if (event.detail.successful && !event.detail.xhr.getResponseHeader('X-OpenHand-Error')) this.querySelectorAll('textarea, input, button').forEach((el) => el.disabled = true)"
      {{ attrs.render() }}>
  {{ content }}
</form>
